title: @OspreyWGolf Finish 13th at Longhorn Invitational to Wrap Up Fall Season
text: @OspreyWGolf Finish 13th at Longhorn Invitational to Wrap Up Fall Season Story Links AUSTIN, Texas -- The North Florida women's golf team concluded their fall tournament schedule Tuesday finishing 13th in the prestigious Betsy Rawls Longhorn Invitational played at the University of Texas Golf Course (par 72 / 6,298 yards).The Ospreys carded a final round 313 to finish with a 54-hole total of 917. Seniors posted the low rounds of the day, 75 (+3), for UNF. George was the squad's top performer earning a tie for 20th in the medalist competition finishing at 222 for the event.Senior Nathalie Nygren participated in the event as an individual finishing tied for 55th at 233 including a final day score of 75.The tournament field featured seven teams ranked in the Top 50 nationally, including four teams listed in the Top 25. In addition, 13 individuals were ranked in the Top 100 in Golfstat's latest rankings.No. 8 ranked Kent State led the team competition wire-to-wire, finishing with at 5-under 859. No. 37 Texas Tech was second at 867 with No. 21 UNLV (873), tournament host Texas (875) and No. 22 New Mexico (882) filling out the Top 5 finishers. TTU's Gabby Barker claimed the medalist crown with a three-round tally of 211 (-5).North Florida will now take a break from competition for the winter with the Ospreys set to return to action in the annual Hughes Cup match against crosstown rival Jacksonville on Feb. 8, 2016, at TPC Sawgrass.
